<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-09-24T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-09-24T14:00:00-05:00" n="153" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d153">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/1972</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-09-24T15:00:00-04:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">September 24, 1918, 3 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Your August 22, 6 p.m. Should an authentic copy of the texts of the
                                agreement and exchange of notes relating to a loan on the security
                                of the forests and mines in Kirin and Heilungkiang Provinces confirm
                                substantially the texts forwarded with your despatch of July 27 last
                                you will lodge with the Chinese Government a formal protest against
                                the monopolistic features of the said agreement.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>